CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 15, 1941, pg. 3, reads: "Is The Customer Always Right?....Pittsburgh Waitresses Reveal Some Of The Problems They Confront - Business Ethics Demand That Waitresses Reveal Some Of The Problems They Confront - Business Ethics Demand That Waitresses Please and Pamper Customers...But It Isn't Always Easy!...In picture No. 1, Corbel Harding waitress waits for Rosabelle...If Rosabelle...much time......Photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Waitress Corbel Harding taking order of woman named Rosabelle seated in booth and holding menu for Rosen's Sandwich Shop
